Fresh Pi session: REPOSITORY CONSTRAINTS AND BRANCH NAME ONLY.

Inputs:
- Prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Approved use case: latest file under {{run.dir}}/use-case/
- Initial test list: {{run.dir}}/test-list/scenarios-initial.md
- Repository root: {{inputs.repo-root}}
- Requested branch, if supplied: {{inputs.branch}}
- Base branch: {{inputs.base-branch}}

Goal:
Choose a safe branch name and record repository guidance plus an explicit deterministic final-validation plan.

Rules:
- Do not edit repository files.
- Do not produce an upfront implementation design.
- Record applicable repository instructions, normal focused/full test commands, and relevant test locations without choosing an implementation.
- Write a version-1 validation plan containing at least one broad repository check. Prefer argv arrays. Compound shell commands must be explicit strings with `"shell": true`.
- Checks must be non-interactive, bounded by `timeout_seconds` (1–7200), appropriate to run in the future worktree, and free of hidden credentials or external product side effects.
- Use stable unique check ids. The deterministic regression process will combine this plan with all completed focused TDD checks.
- Branch names use lowercase letters, numbers, slashes, and hyphens only.
- Prefer `feature/`, `fix/`, `docs/`, `refactor/`, `test/`, or `chore/`; never use `agent/`.
- Honor a valid requested branch; otherwise derive a concise semantic name.

Write:
- Constraints: {{run.dir}}/design/repository-constraints.md
- Validation plan: {{run.dir}}/design/validation-plan.json
- Branch: {{run.dir}}/design/branch-name.txt
- Status: {{run.dir}}/design/status-{{run.round}}.json

Validation-plan shape:
{"version":1,"checks":[{"id":"full-suite","command":["bb","test"],"timeout_seconds":1800}]}

For a compound command only:
{"version":1,"checks":[{"id":"ci-equivalent","command":"npm ci && bb test && npm run web:test","shell":true,"timeout_seconds":3600}]}

Status:
{"status":"pass","summary":"branch and repository constraints ready","issues_file":null}
